5000|$|The FIL European Luge Championships 2008 {{took place}} January 7-13, 2008 at the Cesana Pariol track in Cesana, Italy. The relay {{competition}} took {{the place of}} the team event that had been held at every European championship since 1988. This event had all teams start at the same part of the track (located at the women's singles/ men's doubles start house), then run down to the finish and tap on a <b>relay</b> <b>marker</b> to exchange from one slider on a team to the next (men's doubles to women's singles to men's singles) with the fastest time winning.|$|E
50|$|The FIL World Luge Championships 2008 {{took place}} January 21-27, 2008 at the bobsleigh, luge, and {{skeleton}} track in Oberhof, Germany {{for the third}} time after having hosted the event in 1973 and 1985. The relay competition took the place of the team event that had been held at every world championship since 1989. This event had all of teams start at the same part of the track (located at the women's singles/ men's doubles start house), then run down to the finish and tap on a <b>relay</b> <b>marker</b> to exchange from one slider on a team to the next (men's doubles to women's singles to men's singles) with the fastest time winning.|$|E

